headlines.description: — Zach LaVine had 25 points and 10 rebounds, Domantas Sabonis added 24 points, 11 rebounds and seven assists and the Sacramento Kings rolled past the Charlotte Hornets 125-102 on Friday night to remain in 10th place in the Western Conference standings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings beat Hornets 125-102 to maintain hold on 10th spot in the West

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 31 points and hit three 3-pointers and the Boston Celtics broke the NBA record for...
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics break NBA season 3s record in 123-103 victory over the Suns

headlines.description: — Tim Hardaway Jr. scored 23 points, Jalen Duren had 21 points and 18 rebounds and the Detroit Pistons beat the Toronto Raptors 117-105 on Friday night to wrap up their first playoff berth since 2018-19.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons wrap up their first playoff spot since 2018-19 with 117-105 victory over the Raptors

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic and Coby White each had 31 points, Josh Giddey had a triple-double and the post-season bound Chicago Bulls beat the Portland Trail Blazers 118-113 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic, White, Giddey lead the post-season bound Bulls past the Trail Blazers, 118-113

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Jalen Green had 34 points, Alperen Sengun added 31 and the Houston Rockets snapped the Oklahoma City Thunder's 11-game winning streak with a 125-111 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green scores 34 as Rockets snap Thunder's 11-game winning streak with 125-111 victory

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 26 points, Evan Mobley added 25 points and 10 rebounds and the Cleveland Cavaliers held on to beat the San Antonio Spurs 114-113 on Friday to move a game away from clinching the best record in the Eastern Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell, Mobley help Cavaliers beat Spurs 114-113, close within a game of sealing East's best mark

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 36 points and the Golden State Warriors beat the Denver Nuggets 118-104 on Friday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 36 points as Warriors beat Nuggets 118-104 for fifth straight win

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 35 points, Austin Reaves added 30 and LeBron James had 27 in the Los Angeles Lakers' 124-108 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic bounces back to lead the Lakers to a 124-108 victory over the Pelicans

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 20 points, Ivica Zubac had 14 points and 13 rebounds and the Los Angeles Clippers routed the Dallas Mavericks 114-91 on Friday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard scores 20 points to help Clippers rout Mavericks 114-91 for 3rd straight win
